summary:
Some functions (especially in display.c) use hand-tuned software pipelining GCC won't reproduce. A single monolithic `__asm__("....")` block reads as cheating ('just renaming the wrapper'). Per-instruction `asm volatile` calls inside a C function let GCC schedule the surrounding C while specific instructions stay verbatim.

Pattern:
```c
register s32 t0 asm("$t0");
register s32 t1 asm("$t1");

asm volatile("multu %0, %1" :: "r"(a), "r"(b));
asm volatile("mflo %0" : "=r"(t0));
/* C code can interleave between asm calls */
asm volatile("andi %0, %1, 0xffff" : "=r"(t1) : "r"(t0));
```

This is a project-accepted pattern, distinct from the rejected single inline asm block.
